com.stormpath.sdk.api

Interface ApiRequestAuthenticator

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    OauthRequestAuthenticator

    public interface ApiRequestAuthenticator
    Authenticates an API HTTP Request and returns a result.
    Since:
    1.0.RC
    See Also:
    Application.authenticateApiRequest(Object), execute()

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ApiAuthenticationResult execute()
      Returns an ApiAuthenticationResult after a successful authentication to an HTTP API endpoint.

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        ApiAuthenticationResult execute()
        Returns an ApiAuthenticationResult after a successful authentication to an HTTP API endpoint.

        The concrete type of the authentication result will depend on the request type, and can be resolved to the specific type using a AuthenticationResultVisitor.

        Returns:
        ApiAuthenticationResult if the API request was authenticated successfully.
        See Also:
        Application.authenticateApiRequest(Object), Application.authenticateOauthRequest(Object)
